# chunk_corner_ao.tas — Regression test for AO / face-culling correctness at
# chunk corners.
#
# Problem fixed: when chunk A loaded after its diagonal neighbour B was already
# meshed, B's corner vertices (whose AO samples reach into A) were computed
# while A was missing — `isSolid` returned false for A's blocks, giving those
# vertices too-bright AO.  `generateChunk` now marks all 8 surrounding chunks
# dirty (previously only 4 face-adjacent), so B re-meshes once A arrives.
# Similarly `setBlock` now dirtied neighbours within AO reach (2 cells).
#
# This TAS digs a 2×2 pit that straddles the chunk boundary at x=16
# (chunk 0 / chunk 1 in the X axis).  Both sides of the pit are in different
# chunks but share a corner, so the wall-face AO at the join is affected by
# the fix.  The captured frame serves as a regression baseline: if the fix
# is reverted, the corner vertex brightness will differ.
#
# Spawn is at approximately (24, 65, 20) on the default flatland world.
# The chunk boundary is at world x=16.  We walk left (−X) to reach it.
#
# Usage (from utils/swindowzig):
#   zig build native -Dexample=voxel
#   ./zig-out/bin/voxel --world=flatland --aa=none --render-distance=4 \
#     --ao=moore --lighting=skylight \
#     --tas examples/voxel/tests/chunk_corner_ao.tas \
#     --dump-frame=/tmp/chunk_corner_ao.ppm

# --- Capture mouse ---
1 mouse_down left
2 mouse_up left

# --- Look straight down so we can dig at our feet ---
3 mouse_move 0 180

# --- Walk left (−X) toward the chunk boundary at x=16 ---
# Hold A for ~30 ticks to cross from x≈24 to x≈16
5  key_down a
35 key_up a

# --- Dig once to open a hole at the boundary ---
37 mouse_down left
38 mouse_up left

# --- Walk a little further to straddle the boundary, dig again ---
40 key_down a
48 key_up a
50 mouse_down left
51 mouse_up left

# --- Step back and look at the pit from an angle so the AO on the pit walls
#     (including the corner where both chunks meet) is visible ---
53 key_down s
60 key_up s
62 mouse_move 0 -60
63 mouse_move 4 0
64 mouse_move 4 0
65 mouse_move 4 0
66 mouse_move 4 0

# Hold steady for dump-frame
75 mouse_move 0 0
